(3) After receipt of an application in terms of subsection (2), the surveyor concerned shall survey the vessel for the purpose of determining— (a) whether the vessel is seaworthy; (b) whether she is equipped in accordance with the provisions of this Act; (c) her description, tonnage, dimensions, name and method of propulsion; (d) the geographical limits or areas of inland waters outside which the vessel may not be used having regard to her construction, suitability for navigation and safe operation; (e) the maximum number of passengers and the maximum quantity of cargo to be carried therein; (f) the crew to be carried therein and standards of competency to be attained by members of such crew ; (g) such further matters as may be prescribed.
