(3) As soon as the requirements of this Act preliminary to registration have been complied with, the registrar of vessels to whom application for registration has been made shall enter in the register of vessels for his port— (a) where applicable, the details comprised in the surveyor's certificate ; (b) the name and address of the registered owner ; (c) where applicable, the name and address of the master ; and shall issue to the owner a certificate of registration setting out the particulars respecting the vessel in the register of vessels and such other particulars as may be prescribed.
